The paper deals with the design of multiple antenna cognitive radio networks, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), system and control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and computer networks (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the coexistence constraint, which is a key issue in cognitive radio networks, and proposes a joint design of various components to minimize the sum mean square error of the secondary user system. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT, followed by cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.CR.
